===message:I agree with Debbie and Robert's statement and how it compares with situation today verses 100 years ago. But, I also like to add the crime status versus 100 years ago.
Crime today has the number one rating in America with the copycat abduction, raping, and murder of our little girls playing outside of their homes, innocent people dying due to robbery, and domestic violence.
People who lived 100 years ago had their problem but it does not compare to the "HELL" we live in today. They didn't have to fight terrorists and worry about if any one has high-jack a plane and crash it into a building.
The anniversary of the innocent victims who died on September 11 is coming soon, what else evil do America have to sustain.
So Yes, I believed that people who lived 100 years ago was better off than we are today.
