===subject:Post 2
===from:Jason Odom
===date:Thu Oct  3  8:50:52 2002
===message:I agree that people certainly could live without all of the technological advances and luxuries that we have today. It would take some getting used to, but it always takes people some time to adjust to a changing society. When the technology that we enjoy today was in its beginnings, the people of that time had to adjust to being able to complete tasks more efficiently. People that had never used a microwave had to adjust there cooking and eating habits to incorporate the convenience of a microwave into their lives. We live our lives the way we do today because we have the technological advances to live a certain way. However, the people 100 years ago lived without this advanced technology and were able to survive.
